        "body": "Additive foundation for a SQLite-backed Memory v2 sidecar and two pipelines\n(ingest, rerank). Every surface is wired behind a plugin-config flag and\ndefaults to **off**, so this PR is behaviorally a no-op until a workspace\nopts in via `memoryV2.ingest.enabled` / `memoryV2.rerank.enabled`.\n\n## Why\n\nMemory v2 aims to let `memory-core` track per-location signals (salience,\npinned/superseded status, last-access recency) alongside the existing\nmarkdown files, and rerank `memory_search` results with those signals. This\nPR lands the foundation without changing existing behavior.\n\n## Slices (6 commits, intentionally atomic)\n\n1. **Slice 0 — Sidecar foundation** (`2523e5a7`)\n   `memory/v2-sidecar.db` schema + repo + `openSidecarDatabase`. No\n   consumers yet.\n\n2. **Slice 1a — Ingest internals** (`d1e9f3b0`)\n   Dedupe, extract, handler, normalize, secret-filter, synthetic-ref.\n   Pure module; not registered.\n\n3. **Slice 1b — Ingest wiring** (`eb3d250e`)\n   `registerMemoryV2Ingest(api)` subscribes to `agent_end`. Reads\n   `memoryV2.ingest.enabled` via a type-guarded config check; returns a\n   noop subscription when the flag is off.\n\n4. **Slice 1.5 — Location keys + shadow-touch helper** (`1d33d0ad`)\n   Canonical `memoryLocationId` / path normalization, `recordTouchedLocations`\n   helper. Prerequisite for both rerank lookup and future shadow-row writes.\n\n5. **Slice 2a — Rerank module** (`a1319c00`)\n   `buildRerankWrapper`, `applyRerank`, `loadSidecarSignalsByLocations`.\n   Pure module; not wired.\n\n6. **Slice 2b — Rerank wiring** (`1e4431b6`)\n   `createMemorySearchTool` gains an optional `rerank?: RerankFn`. When the\n   plugin config enables rerank, `buildMemoryV2Rerank(api)` returns a\n   `RerankFn` that is threaded into the tool factory. When off, the rerank\n   field isn't even spread into the options bag — the call path is\n   byte-identical to before.\n\n## Safety properties\n\n- **Default off**, enforced by explicit `=== true` check in both wirings.\n  Truthy coercion (`1`, `\"true\"`) does not enable.\n- **Type-guarded config reads** — malformed `memoryV2.*` never throws;\n  it silently degrades to disabled.\n- **Identity fallback on any rerank error** — `buildRerankWrapper` wraps\n  its sidecar db calls in `try/catch` and returns original results on\n  failure. A broken sidecar cannot break `memory_search`.\n- **Per-workspace db cache** inside the wrapper closure; one `DatabaseSync`\n  per `workspaceDir` per plugin activation.\n- **Additive manifest** — `memoryV2.rerank` is a new object under the\n  sibling `memoryV2.ingest` block added in Slice 1b; no existing keys\n  changed.\n\n## Upstream / update-survival notes\n\nThe hunk most likely to cause future rebase friction is the 13-line\npre-sort block in `extensions/memory-core/src/tools.ts` (the `merged`/\n`reranked` intermediate between result-merge and `.toSorted(...)`). That\narea of the file has seen active upstream work (#67277, #65068). The hunk\nis additive and flag-gated, so a conflict resolution is mechanical:\nre-inject the `merged` intermediate and the conditional `reranked` call.\n\nThe rest of the surface is either:\n- Low-churn (`openclaw.plugin.json` interior addition, `tools.test.ts`\n  end-of-file append), or\n- Contained in new files under `src/memory-v2/` that have no upstream\n  counterpart.\n\n## Known follow-ups (explicitly out of scope here)\n\n- Seam hardening for `api.pluginConfig: unknown`, which is declared as a\n  local type in both `ingest-wiring.ts` and `rerank-wiring.ts`. If the\n  SDK renames the field, both wirings silently see `undefined` and stay\n  disabled. A future small PR can replace the local type with the real\n  SDK register-API type.\n- \"Shadow-only\" mode: currently `shadowOnRecall` only runs when rerank\n  itself is enabled. Collecting training signal before flipping rerank\n  on would need a separate path.\n- Cosmetic: `tools.ts:304` uses `merged as never` to bridge the union\n  element type to `RerankableResult`. `as readonly RerankableResult[]`\n  would be clearer. Not included to keep this PR scoped to feature work.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-memory.config.ts` → 62 files / 643 passed / 3 skipped, 0 failed\n- [x] `pnpm exec tsc -p extensions/memory-core/tsconfig.json --noEmit` → clean\n- [x] `pnpm exec oxlint` on all touched files → 0 warnings, 0 errors\n- [x] `pnpm check` (full repo gate: no-conflict-markers, tool-display, host-env-policy:swift, import-cycles, madge-import-cycles, tsgo, extension-package-boundary, lint, webhook/auth lints) → all 11 gates clean\n",
